We treat rank scoring for document skipping differently from the final result ranking. Namely we keep two top- $\mathbf { 
abla } \cdot k$ rank score thresholds during index traversal. One is based on BM25 weights, another is based on the learned weights. To accomplish that, each posting record in the inverted index contains two weights for each term in a document. A retriever can maintain two queues for active top- $\mathbf { 
abla } \cdot k$ results based on the above two weight types. • Bound estimation for skipping can be influenced by both BM25 and learned weights. Since we maintain two thresholds, we can use one threshold to skip based on BM25 or BM25-influenced score as discussed below, and another to remove documents that will not appear in the final top- $\mathbf { 
abla } \cdot k$ list.
